# ============================================================
# Knowledge Base Settings — single source of truth for vault paths
# ============================================================
# Copy this file to `.claude/knowledge-base.local.md` and fill in your paths.
# This file is gitignored — each team member has their own copy.
#
# Claude will ask you for these values on first run if the file doesn't exist,
# then write your answers here.
# ============================================================

# Absolute path to your knowledge base root.
# Examples:
#   macOS Obsidian local:   /Users/you/Obsidian/MyVault
#   Google Drive (macOS):   /Users/you/Library/CloudStorage/GoogleDrive-you@example.com/My Drive/vault
#   OneDrive (macOS):       /Users/you/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-Personal/vault
#   OneDrive (Windows):     C:/Users/you/OneDrive/vault
vault_path: <ABSOLUTE_PATH_TO_YOUR_VAULT>

# Subdirectory inside the vault that holds your main workspace (optional).
# Leave as-is or delete if you don't use a sub-directory structure.
company_dir: <YOUR_WORKSPACE_SUBDIR>



# Knowledge Base Settings

All vault path variables are defined in the frontmatter above. This file is
the **single source of truth** for knowledge base paths in this project.

When Claude needs to read or write vault content, it loads this file and
resolves paths from the frontmatter — never hardcode vault paths in other
files or prompts.
